the werewolves might expect you to protect them and kill someone else. In general, you should avoid revealing your identity unless absolutely necessary.\n\n\n\n\nYou are Judith, your role in this game is guard.\nWerewolf game starting. Initializing day-night cycle.\nSYSTEM: Starting day-night cycle for Day 1\nSYSTEM: Night 1 begins. Werewolves and special roles take actions.\nGuard action processed. Thelma is protected this night.\nGuard has chosen to protect a player.\nWerewolves have chosen their target.\nSeer has checked a player's identity.\nWitch has made her decision on potion use.\nSYSTEM: Day 1 begins. Players discuss and vote on potential suspects.\nNo candidates decided to run for sheriff. No sheriff in this game anymore.\nNo players deceased during the night.\nChris's speech: Good morning, everyone. I want to start by thanking all of you for your trust and cooperation. It's clear that we all share the same goal of eliminating the werewolves and protecting our village. Last night, I used my antidote to save someone, and I'm relieved to report that the night was peaceful. This is a good sign, but we must remain vigilant. Let's work together to identify and eliminate the werewolves before they can harm us. I believe that by sharing information and supporting each other, we can overcome this threat.\nFrances's speech: Thank you, Chris, for your update. It's reassuring to hear that the night was peaceful, and I appreciate your use of the antidote to save someone. Could you perhaps share a bit more about the player you saved? I believe it's crucial for us to gather as much information as possible to identify the werewolves. Let's all stay vigilant and share any information we have. Together, we can overcome this threat and protect our village.\nJacob's speech: Thank you, Chris, for your update and for using your antidote to save someone. It's reassuring to hear that the night was peaceful. Frances, I agree with your point about the need for more information. While Chris's actions are commendable, we should all strive to gather as much information as possible to identify the werewolves. I haven't noticed anything suspicious yet, but I'll keep a close eye on everyone. Let's all share our observations and work together to protect our village. Together, we can overcome this threat.\nJacqueline's speech: Thank you, Chris, for using your antidote to save someone and for your reassurance that the night was peaceful. Frances, I appreciate your request for more information. I can confirm that I checked Juan last night, and he is not a werewolf. This is a positive sign, but we must remain vigilant. Let's all share our observations and work together to identify the werewolves. By staying united and informed, we can protect our village and eliminate the threat.\nJuan's speech: Thank you, Jacqueline, for checking me last night and confirming that I am not a werewolf. I appreciate your trust in me and the village's efforts to stay vigilant. Last night, I noticed that Chris used their antidote to save someone, which is a positive sign. I also observed that Frances and Jacob seemed attentive and focused on gathering information, which is crucial for our survival. Let's all continue to share our observations and work together to identify the werewolves. By staying united and informed, we can protect our village and eliminate the threat.\nJudith's speech: Thank you all for your contributions and for staying vigilant. I want to confirm that Thelma was the one Chris saved last night, and she is safe. This is a positive sign, but we must remain cautious. As the Guard, I can assure you that I protected someone last night to ensure their safety. Let's all continue to share our observations and work together to identify the werewolves. By staying united and informed, we can protect our village and eliminate the threat.\nJudith's speech: Thank you all for your contributions and for staying vigilant. I want to confirm that Thelma was the one Chris