rming that Chris used their antidote to save Thelma. Your actions as the Guard are crucial for our survival, and I trust that you are doing everything you can to protect us. Jacqueline, I appreciate your efforts in checking Juan and confirming that he is not a werewolf. This is a positive sign, but we must remain vigilant and gather more information. Let's all continue to share our observations and work together to identify the werewolves. By staying united and informed, we can protect our village and eliminate the threat.\nAll players have completed their speeches for today.\nNo player was banished due to a tie.\nBanishment votes:\nJacob voted for Chris\nJudith voted for abstain\nKathleen voted for Judith\nThelma voted for Jacob\nChris voted for Frances\nJacqueline voted for Chris\nJuan voted for Frances\nFrances voted for abstain\nTanya voted for Judith\n(Note: The voting order reflects only the system's query sequence and does not imply any strategic alignment or motive.)\nSYSTEM: Starting day-night cycle for Day 2\nSYSTEM: Night 2 begins. Werewolves and special roles take actions.\n\nHere's the current game state:\n\n{\n  \"days\": 2,\n  \"day/night\": \"night\",\n  \"alive_players\": [\n    \"Jacob\",\n    \"Judith\",\n    \"Kathleen\",\n    \"Thelma\",\n    \"Chris\",\n    \"Jacqueline\",\n    \"Juan\",\n    \"Frances\",\n    \"Tanya\"\n  ],\n  \"sheriff\": null\n}\n\nNow, as a guard, it is your turn to take action.\nHere's the list of people alive:\n<<player_alive_info>>\nLast night, you have protected <<night info>>. You cannot protect him again this night.\nYou can protect one player from being attacked by the werewolves tonight. However, you cannot protect the same player on consecutive nights. As the guard, your role is crucial in preventing the werewolves from killing a key player. If you successfully protect the person targeted by the werewolves, their attack will fail, and no one will die that night. This gives your team an advantage and allows the pro