the werewolves might expect you to protect them and kill someone else. In general, you should avoid revealing your identity unless absolutely necessary.\n\n\n\n\nYou are Chris, your role in this game is witch.\nWerewolf game starting. Initializing day-night cycle.\nSYSTEM: Starting day-night cycle for Day 1\nSYSTEM: Night 1 begins. Werewolves and special roles take actions.\nGuard has chosen to protect a player.\nWerewolves have chosen their target.\nSeer has checked a player's identity.\nWitch used antidote to save Chris.\nWitch has made her decision on potion use.\nSYSTEM: Day 1 begins. Players discuss and vote on potential suspects.\nNo candidates decided to run for sheriff. No sheriff in this game anymore.\nNo players deceased during the night.\nChris's speech: Good morning, everyone. I want to start by thanking all of you for your trust and cooperation. It's clear that we all share the same goal of eliminating the werewolves and protecting our village. Last night, I used my antidote to save someone, and I'm relieved to report that the night was peaceful. This is a good sign, but we must remain vigilant. Let's work together to identify and eliminate the werewolves before they can harm us. I believe that by sharing information and supporting each other, we can overcome this threat.\nChris's speech: Good morning, everyone. I want to start by thanking all of you for your trust and cooperation. It's clear that we all share the same goal of eliminating the werewolves and protecting our village. Last night, I used my antidote to save someone, and I'm relieved to report that the night was peaceful. This is a good sign, but we must remain vigilant. Let's work together to identify and eliminate the werewolves before they can harm us. I believe that by sharing information and supporting each other, we can overcome this threat.\nFrances's speech: Thank you, Chris, for your update. It's reassuring to hear that the night was peaceful, and I appreciate your use of the antidote to save someone. Could you perhaps share a bit more about the player you saved? I believe it's crucial for us to gather as much information as possible to identify the werewolves. Let's all stay vigilant and share any information we have. Together, we can overcome this threat and protect our village.\nJacob's speech: Thank you, Chris, for your update and for using your antidote to save someone. It's reassuring to hear that the night was peaceful. Frances, I agree with your point about the need for more information. While Chris's actions are commendable, we should all strive to gather as much information as possible to identify the werewolves. I haven't noticed anything suspicious yet, but I'll keep a close eye on everyone. Let's all share our observations and work together to protect our village. Together, we can overcome this threat.\nJacqueline's speech: Thank you, Chris, for using your antidote to save someone and for your reassurance that the night was peaceful. Frances, I appreciate your request for more information. I can confirm that I checked Juan last night, and he is not a werewolf. This is a positive sign, but we must remain vigilant. Let's all share our observations and work together to identify the werewolves. By staying united and informed, we can protect our village and eliminate the threat.\nJuan's speech: Thank you, Jacqueline, for checking me last night and confirming that I am not a werewolf. I appreciate your trust in me and the village's efforts to stay vigilant. Last night, I noticed that Chris used their antidote to save someone, which is a positive sign. I also observed that Frances and Jacob seemed attentive and focused on gathering information, which is crucial for our survival. Let's all continue to share our observations and work together to identify the werewolves. By staying united and informed, we can protect our village and eliminate the threat.\nJudith's speech: Thank you all for your contributions and for staying vigilant. I want to confirm that Thelma was the one Chris saved last night, and she is safe. This is a positive sign, but we must remain cautious. As the Guard, I can assure you that I protected someone last night to ensure their safety. Let's all continue to share our observations and work together to identify the werewolves. By staying united and informed, we can protect our village and eliminate the threat.\nKathleen's speech: Thank you all for your contributions and for staying vigilant. It's clear that we all share the same goal of eliminating the werewolves and protecting our village. Judith, thank you for confirming that Chris used their antidote to save Thelma. While this is a positive sign, I believe we should remain cautious and not trust anyone too quickly. We need more information to make informed decisions. I noticed that some players, like Frances and Jacob, seemed attentive and focused on gathering information, which is crucial for our survival. Let's all continue to share our observations and work together to identify the werewolves. By staying united and informed, we can protect our village and eliminate the threat.\nTanya's speech: Thank you all for your contributions and for staying vigilant. It's clear that we all share the same goal of eliminating the werewolves and protecting our village. Judith, thank you for confirming that Chris used their antidote to save Thelma and for your efforts as the Guard. Your actions are crucial for our survival, and I trust that you are doing everything you can to protect us. Kathleen, I understand your cautionary tone, and I agree that we need to remain vigilant and gather more information. Let's all continue to share our observations and work together to identify the werewolves. By staying united and informed, we can protect our village and eliminate the threat.\nThelma's speech: Thank you all for your contributions and for staying vigilant. It's clear that we all share the same goal of eliminating the werewolves and protecting our village. Judith, thank you for confirming that Chris used their antidote to save Thelma. Your actions as the Guard are crucial for our survival, and I trust that you are doing everything you can to protect us. Jacqueline, I appreciate your efforts in checking Juan and confirming that he is not a werewolf. This is a positive sign, but we must remain vigilant and gather more information. Let's all continue to share our observations and work together to identify the werewolves. By staying united and informed, we can protect our village and eliminate the threat.\nAll players have completed their speeches for today.\nNo player was banished due to a tie.\nBanishment votes:\nJacob voted for Chris\nJudith voted for abstain\nKathleen voted for Judith\nThelma voted for Jacob\nChris voted for Frances\nJacqueline voted for Chris\nJuan voted for Frances\nFrances voted for abstain\nTanya voted for Judith\n(Note: The voting order reflects only the system's query sequence and does not imply any strategic alignment or motive.)\nSYSTEM: Starting day-night cycle for Day 2\nSYSTEM: Night 2 begins. Werewolves and special roles take actions.\nGuard has chosen to protect a player.\nWerewolves have chosen their target.\nSeer has checked a player's identity.\nWitch used poison on Jacob.\nWitch has made her decision on potion use.\nSYSTEM: Day 2 begins. Players discuss and vote on potential suspects.\nPlayers deceased during the night: Jacqueline, Jacob\nPlayer Jacqueline has been eliminated from the game.\nPlayer Jacob has been eliminated from the game.\n\nHere's the current game state:\n\n{\n  \"days\": 2,\n  \"day/night\": \"day\",\n  \"alive_players\": [\n    \"Judith\",\n    \"Kathleen\",\n    \"Thelma\",\n    \"Chris\",\n    \"Juan\",\n    \"Frances\",\n    \"Tanya\"\n  ],\n  \"sheriff\": null\n}\n\nNow, it is your turn to speak.\nYou are the 1 player to speak this round.\nHere is what the players before you have said:\n\n\nAt this stage, each player is expected to share their opinions and reveal any information they have gathered, helping the group make an informed decision about who to banish next. Follow these steps to organize your thoughts and decide your action:\n\n0. Based on your current role and objectives, what do you need to achieve in order to win? Do you need to gain more trust, deflect suspicion, or accomplish something else? Break down your ultimate goal into smaller, actionable steps you need to complete during this round of speech. Record your plan in role_objectives.\n\n1. Think about your speaking position. You are the 1 player to speak. What have the previous players said? Is there anything that directly impacts your position (e.g., claims against you, information about your role)? Should you respond to their claims? If so, how should you respond? Store your analysis in response_plan.\n\n2. Evaluate the statements made by the players who spoke before you. Whose words seem credible? Who seems suspicious, possibly a werewolf? Should you ally with someone or criticize another player’s statements? Analyze each player’s speech in speech_analysis.\n\n3. What is your main goal for this round? Do you want to provide information, reveal your role, or shift the game's momentum to gain trust? Should you claim a specific role, mislead other players, or offer false information? Based on this, decide what you will say. Record this in goal_strategy.\n\n4. How do you think your speech will be perceived? Will it make you appear more trustworthy, or will it raise suspicion? Consider how others will react to what you say. Record your perception_analysis.\n\n5. **Additional Considerations Based on Your Role**:\n   - If you are the **seer** (or claiming to be one):\n     - Should you reveal who you checked last night and the results of your checks from the previous night? Why or why not? Should you direct the guard or witch on who to protect tonight?\n   - If you are the **guard** (or claiming to be one):\n     - Should you reveal whom you protected last night and who you plan to protect tonight? Will you speak the truth or lie about your protection? Should you coordinate with the witch and the seer?\n   - If you are the **witch**(or claiming to be one, not recommended, since rel witch have a poison which can kill you at night):\n     - Should you reveal your identity? If so, should you reveal who you saved last night (if it was a peaceful night)? Should you discuss the plan for future nights? Will you tell the truth or lie about your actions?\n   - If you are the **sheriff**:\n     - Should you reveal your \"badge flow\" (i.e., who you would pass the sheriff badge to if you were to die)? If you are also the seer, should you reveal who you plan to check tonight? Should you declare what you will do with the badge based on your findings (e.g., pass it to a trusted player, or destroy it if you find a werewolf)?\n   - **If you are a werewolf** :\n     - Should you claim to be a different role? If so, what role should you claim? Has anyone else already claimed this role? How would this affect your credibility? Will this claim deflect suspicion from you or raise doubts? How will other players react to this claim, and will it help you survive longer? What risks are involved if someone else counterclaims or reveals your lie?\n\n6. Based on the above, create a detailed outline of your speech in speech_outline.\n\n7. What is your final decision? Write your complete speech content in action, including your final thoughts on how it should impact the game.\n\n\n=============================[Optional Daily Tasks]=============================\nHere are the tasks relevant to you:\nprotect_seer: Keep the seer alive by focusing on their safety.\nexile_werewolf: Coordinate with others to vote out a suspected werewolf.\nYou may incorporate them if appropriate.\n\nRemember, you are using an independent strategy. Make decisions based on your own judgment, with less reliance on others' input."
