iate your emphasis on trusting the Seer and the Guard, as their roles are crucial for our survival. However, I believe we should remain cautious and verify their findings with other players. The recent eliminations of Jacqueline, Jacob, Frances, and Judith could be strategic moves by the werewolves, so we need to gather more information before making any hasty decisions. Let's all continue to share our observations and work together to identify the werewolves. By staying united and informed, we can protect our village and eliminate the threat. I also want to express my support for the Seer and the Guard's actions, as they are essential for our survival.\n\nHere's the current game state:\n\n{\n  \"days\": 4,\n  \"day/night\": \"day\",\n  \"alive_players\": [\n    \"Kathleen\",\n    \"Thelma\",\n    \"Chris\",\n    \"Tanya\"\n  ],\n  \"sheriff\": null\n}\n\nNow, it is your turn to speak.\nYou are the 3 player to speak this round.\nHere is what the players before you have said:\nChris: Good morning, everyone. I want to start by thanking all of you for your contributions and for staying vigilant. It's clear that we all share the same goal of eliminating the werewolves and protecting our village. The recent eliminations of Jacqueline, Jacob, Frances, and Judith could be strategic moves by the werewolves, so we need to remain cautious and gather more information before making any hasty decisions. Kathleen, I understand your cautious approach and the importance of verifying the Seer's findings. However, I believe that the Seer's information is crucial for our survival, and we should trust their findings. The Seer's role is essential in identifying the werewolves, and we need to support them. Last night, I used my poison on a player, but I will not reveal who it was to avoid compromising my role. The recent eliminations could be strategic moves by the werewolves, so we need to remain cautious and gather more information before making any hasty decisions. Let's all continue 